15 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
16 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 6060.50 of Title 36, unless
17 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
18 As used in this section:
19 1. "Health care service" means any services provided by a
20 health care provider, or by an individual working for or under the
21 supervision of a health care provider, that relate to the diagnosis,
22 assessment, prevention, treatment, or care of any human illness,
23 disease, injury, or condition, as defined by paragraph 2 of Section
24 1-1708.1C of Title 63 of the Oklahoma Statutes.
